The 26-year-old prophet and the teenager were among a group of congregants who had gathered for the event. JOHANNESBURG - Police are investigating after two people drowned in Limpopo. It’s understood a “prophet” and a 16-year-old congregant were allegedly performing a spiritual ceremony at the Ngwedi River in Thohoyandou on Thursday. The 26-year-old prophet and the teenager were among a group of congregants who had gathered for the event. Police spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo said: “Communities members have been warned to be careful when entering the water and they should preferably do so if they are able to swim to prevent similar incidences from happening.”